  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - Due to the siting, design and scale of the proposed shopfront extension and the inclusion of external roller shutters, the proposal would give rise to an incongruous and visually intrusive form of development which would harmful to the visual amenity of the streetscape.  This would harm the character and appearance of the subject building and the wider neighbourhood parade. The development therefore fails to meet the high-quality design aspirations of the National Planning Policy Framework (2021), and is contrary to policies D3(D1 and D11) and D8 (F) of the London Plan (2021), Core Strategy Policy CS1.B (2012) and policies DM1 and DM4 of the Harrow Development Management Policies.",
    "Reason : 2 - The proposal encroaches beyond the curtilage of the site as shown on the submitted site location plan and therefore fails to provide an accurate  plan which identifies the land to which the application relates, contrary to  Article 7.1(c)(i) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015 (as amended)."
  ],
